result.formatted_address: 65 Wan Chai Rd, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: Joyous Restaurant

reviews.text: Excellent place for food. Good value. Definitely a place for repeat visits

Came here for a late satay beef instant noodle breakfast during the week. Service was as efficient as Hong Kong service can be but also pleasantly surprised with the friendly tones and smiles from the service workers. Prices are affordable, food was good. Would visit again if in the area. Only thing was that my friend got a breakfast that included the buttered corn which was way tooo buttery.
Steam ribs and veggie soup are delicious

We live in the area and just wanted to try something different.  Food was good, tasty, sizable dishes and fairly priced.  Service was terrific, partly due to me being western and the menu being only in Chinese. Considering Joyous's location on the fringe of Wanchai Market area, and with so many tourists around, there probably should be an English menu, but if there is, they didn't offer it.  Also -- a small thing, but even so -- the menu is confusing, about what dishes can actually be ordered, and at what times of day, and on what dates.  Never saw anything like that before.

But what we had was good, and staff were friendly, and it didn't break the bank.  Would I go back?  Yes, but always with someone who can navigate the menu.

Best cha chan teng restaurant in wanchai with very good choice and good quality food and good "al dente" macaroni every time and very nice staff too.
Ask for the english menu if u want specific info else just order by the pictures!
✌😎🙏

result.name: 嘗樂

reviews.text: 街市中的美味茶餐廳😋👍
餐牌每兩個月更換一次，更新频密目的是顯然是在每次更新均可以調整餐價。一年來更換了六次，觀察到至小加了三至四次價，十分狼胎。市面上一般食市一年只調價一次。
食物質素有水準，服務等等各方面都保持水準
食物味道與價錢合理，但晚市不設「碟頭飯」套餐，動輒近百或過百每位，但只是港式茶餐廳🤔
街坊小菜…幾好
